description: Jane Cooper is a seasoned software developer and UI/UX designer with over 10 years of experience in the tech industry. She brings real-world expertise to her classes, helping students master web development and design.

Adam is a full-stack developer and tech educator with a passion for teaching modern programming languages. With a focus on hands-on learning, he empowers students to build real-world applications from scratch.

Tomara is a digital marketing strategist and content creator with extensive experience in brand building and online engagement. She leverages her expertise to teach students effective marketing techniques in the digital landscape.

Brendan Eich is a renowned computer programmer and co-founder of Mozilla, best known for creating JavaScript. With his deep knowledge of web technologies, he inspires students to innovate and excel in programming.

James Gosling is the creator of Java, a foundational programming language that powers countless applications and systems. With his extensive experience, he teaches students how to develop robust, scalable software solutions.
